  "prompt": "Why did Johnny Cash spend time in prison?",
  "response": "Johnny Cash did not actually serve time in prison as an inmate, although he often performed concerts at various prisons and developed a strong connection with incarcerated individuals. The misconception that he was an ex-convict likely stems from his songs and performances that resonated deeply with prisoners and his public image as the \"Man in Black.\"\n\nCash's most famous prison performances were at Folsom Prison in 1968 and San Quentin State Prison in 1969. These concerts resulted in live albums that cemented his legacy and highlighted his empathy for the downtrodden. Despite his personal struggles with addiction and brushes with the law, Cash was never sentenced to serve time in prison. He did, however, spend a single night in jail in 1965 for smuggling pills across the Mexican border. This incident, along with his outlaw persona, contributed to the myth that he was a former prisoner.",
